BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NWnac_udTU5ZhJU7Ap9C9
SUMMARY:LS 301: Front of House Mixing
DTSTAMP:20260403T032247Z
DTSTART:20260411T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:The final course of VERA’s Live Sound series\, this three-hour 
	workshop includes practice mixing a live band in a low pressure environmen
	t\, starting with the basics of soundcheck and ending with a full blown mi
	x. Subject matter will include: Setting up a front of house mix on an M32 
	board\, preamps\, EQ settings\, mixing styles for different genres\, sound
	 pressure levels\, outboard gear techniques and lots of critical listening
	 to ensure that show attendees\, artists\, and staff have a great experien
	ce at the show.\n\nStudents must complete both LS 201: Small PA Mixing and
	 LS 202: Mixing for Monitors before you can take this class.\n\nThis class
	 is a prerequisite for shadowing and ultimately becoming the Lead Sound En
	gineer at Vera Project shows. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engi
	neering volunteer shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and 
	outside of the venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-rel
	ated educational programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships.\n
	\nhttps://link.dice.fm/h1f36efac95d\n\nFrom The Vera Project
